TJX Cos Inc, the owner of off-price chains T.J. Maxx and Marshalls, on Tuesday posted its slowest comparable-store sales growth in more than 10 quarters, adding to the gloom in the retail industry. Shares of the company dipped nearly 5 percent to $73.3 before the bell.













						                            
